# Second Brain - Implementation Walkthrough

## Summary

Built a **fully offline, local-first personal assistant** Android app with a **chat-style interface**, **rule-based NLP parser**, **Room database**, **alarm-based reminders**, **daily idea resurfacing**, and a **placeholder AI module** for future on-device LLM integration.

**23 Kotlin source files** created across 7 packages, plus unit tests, resources, and Gradle configuration.

---

## Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph UI["ui/ (Jetpack Compose)"]
        MA[MainActivity] --> CS[ChatScreen]
        CS --> CV[ChatViewModel]
    end

    subgraph Domain["domain/ (Use Cases)"]
        CV --> PU[ProcessUserInputUseCase]
    end

    subgraph Parser["parser/ (NLP)"]
        PU --> RBP[RuleBasedParser]
    end

    subgraph AI["ai/ (Optional)"]
        PU -.-> LLM["LocalLlmEngine (placeholder)"]
    end

    subgraph Data["data/ (Room)"]
        PU --> MR[MemoryRepository]
        MR --> MD[MemoryDao]
        MD --> DB[(SQLite DB)]
    end

    subgraph Scheduler["scheduler/ (Background)"]
        PU --> AS[AlarmScheduler]
        AS --> RR[ReminderReceiver]
        BR[BootReceiver] --> AS
        IRW[IdeaResurfacingWorker] --> MR
    end
```

